\c 19
\s1 Peraturan-Peraturan Lainnya
\p
\v 1 TUHAN menyuruh Musa berbicara kepada orang-orang Israel demikian:
\p
\v 2 “Beritahukanlah kepada bangsa Israel agar supaya mereka harus hidup dengan sopan dan kudus sebab Aku Allah yang kudus.
\p
\v 3 “Setiap orang harus menghormati kedua orang tuanya, baik bapa dan ibunya dan menjaga/menghormati hari Sabat yang sudah Aku perintahkan. Sebab Aku inilah TUHAN-mu.
\p
\v 4 Janganlah kami menyembah berhala. Jangan membuat patung dalam bentuk dan terbuat dari apapun untuk disembah. Sebab Aku inilah TUHAN-mu.
\p
\v 5 Kalau kamu hendak mempersembahkan korban dari hewan tertentu maka kamu harus melalukannya sesuai dengan aturan yang Aku sudah tentukan.
\v 6 Daging korban itu harus dimakan atau boleh juga disimpan sampai besok hari, tetapi jangan sampai lebih dari itu. Kalau sudah tiga hari maka harus dibakar habis.
\v 7 Karena daging yang sudah lebih dari dua hari adalah haram dan Aku tidak terima itu lain.
\v 8 Barang siapa yang makan daging binatang itu akan dipersalahkan dan kesalahannya ditanggung sendiri sebab sudah tidak menghargai peraturan-peraturan yang ditetapkan.
\v 9 Kalau musim panen dan kamu memanen hasil di ladangmu. Maka jangan potong semua gandum yang tumbuh di pinggir ladangmu dan jangan
\p kembali untuk mengumpulkan sisa-sisanya.
\v 10 Kalau musim panen dan kamu memanen hasil di ladangmu. Maka jangan potong semua gandum yang tumbuh di pinggir ladangmu dan jangan kembali untuk mengumpulkan sisa-sisanya.
\p
\v 11 Jangan kamu mencuri, menipu dan berdusta.
\p
\v 12 Jangan bersumpah dengan menyebutkan nama Tuhan dan hormatilah nama TUHANmu.
\p
\v 13 Jangan melakukan kecurangan pada orang lemah.
\p
\v 14 Jangan membuat susah orang cacat dan jangan taruh sesuatu yang menghalangi jalannya.
\p
\v 15 Selalu menghargai orang, jangan mengadili mereka dengan tidak adil
\p
\v 16 Jangan menyebarkan berita bohong di antara sesama.
\p
\v 17 Jangan membenci sesama, tegurlah dengan rendah hari apabila ada yang orang yang salah paham terhadap kita.
\p
\v 18 Jangan menyimpan dendam kepada orang lain, tetapi seharusnya kamu harus mengasihi dia seperti diri sendiri.
\p
\v 19 Peliharalah peraturan-peraturan dari TUHAN.
\p
\v 20 If a man has sex with a slave woman who has been promised to marry some other man, but she has not been bought by that man and is still a slave, the man who had sex with her must be punished. But because she is still a slave, she and the man who had sex with her must not be killed.
\v 21 However, that man must bring a ram to \add be slaughtered at\add* the entrance of the Sacred Tent area, to be an offering in order that he no longer be guilty for his sin.
\v 22 The priest will offer that ram to me in order that the man will be forgiven for the sin that he committed, and I will forgive him.
\p
\v 23 When you enter the land \add that I have promised to give toyou\add*, and when you plant various kinds of fruit trees, you must not eat any of their fruit for three years [DOU].
\v 24 In the fourth year all of their fruit must be set aside to belong to me; it must be brought to me to be an offering to praise me.
\v 25 But in the fifth/next year, you will be permitted to eat their fruit. If you do that, your trees will produce much fruit.I, Yahweh your God, \add am promising that\add*.
\p
\v 26 Do not eat any meat that still has \add the animal's\add* blood in it.
\p Do not consult spirits to find out what will happen in the future, and do not practice sorcery.
\p
\v 27 Do not shave the hair at the sides of your heads \add like pagan peopledo\add*.
\p
\v 28 Do not cut your bodies \add when you are mourning\add* for people who have died, and do not put tattoos on your bodies.I, Yahweh your God, \add am commanding this\add*.
\p
\v 29 Do not disgrace your daughters by forcing them to become prostitutes. If you cause them to become prostitutes, soon the land will be filled with prostitutes and all other kinds of people's wicked behavior.
\p
\v 30 Honor my Sabbath days and revere my Sacred Tent, because I, Yahweh,\add live there\add*.
\p
\v 31 Do not seek advice from those who ◄consult/talk with► the spirits of dead people [DOU], because if you do that, they willdefile you. I, Yahweh your God, \add am the one you should consult\add*.
\p
\v 32 Stand up when old people \add enter the room\add*, and show that you respect them, and also revere me, your God; that iswhat I, Yahweh, \add am commanding\add*.
\p
\v 33 When foreigners live among you \add in your land\add*, do not mistreat them.
\v 34 You must treat them like you treat your fellow-citizens. Love them like you love yourselves, and do not forget that oncewhen you were foreigners in Egypt \add you were badly mistreated by the people ofEgypt\add*. I, Yahweh your God, \add am commanding you to do this\add*.
\p
\v 35 When you are measuring things, to see how long they are or how much they weigh or how many there are,
\v 36 use correct \add measuring sticks and\add* scales and weights\add on the scales\add* and measuring baskets and other measuring containers. I Yahweh, your God, who brought you out of Egypt,\add am giving you these laws.\add*
\p
\v 37 Obey carefully [DOU] all my laws and decrees, because I, Yahweh,\add am the one who am commanding them\add*.”